    <h2>How does it work?</h2>
    <p>We monitor the dependencies your application depends on. Right now this means you install our <b>tiny</b> agent. It's written in golang and it's <b><a href="https://github.com/appcanary/agent" target="_blank">entirely open source</a></b>.
    </p>
    <p>You tell us which files list your server's dependencies, and we keep track of them. Whenever you make a deploy - or new packages are installed - we find out. 

      <h2>Getting started</h2>
      <h4>
      <ul class="install-nav">
        <li>
          Using chef
        </li>
         <li>
          Using puppet
        </li>
         <li>
          Manual installation
        </li>
      </ul>
      </h4>
        
    <h3>Install manually:</h3>
    <section>

    <div class="onboard-box">
      <div class="onboard-wrapper">
        <section style="border: none">
          <div class="onboard-title">
            <h3>5 minute install:</h3>
            <br/>
            <h4>Using chef/puppet</h4>
            <p>We've published libraries for both chef and puppet. 
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Chef</strong>: You can find our cookbook <a href="https://supermarket.chef.io/cookbooks/appcanary" target="_blank">on the supermarket</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Puppet</strong>: You can find our module <a href="https://forge.puppetlabs.com/appcanary/appcanary" target="_blank">on the forge</a>.</li>
              </ul>

              Each corresponding page will have instructions on how to add it to your own deployment. 
              <br/>
              <br/>
              In both cases you will want the following api key:
              <kbd>
                <%= @agent_token %>
              </kbd>
            </p>

            <br/>
            <h4>Manual installation</h4>

            <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
              <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#deb" data-toggle="tab"><%= image_tag "icon-ubuntu.png", :style => "width: 13px"%> Ubuntu and <%= image_tag "icon-debian.png", :style => "width: 13px"%> Debian</a></li>
              <li role="presentation"><a href="#rpm" data-toggle="tab"><%= image_tag "icon-redhat.png", :style => "width: 13px"%> Redhat, <%= image_tag "icon-centos.png", :style => "width: 13px"%> CentOS and Amazon</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <div class="onboard-desc">
            <div class="tab-content">
              <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="deb">
                <%= render :partial => "debian" %>
              </div>

              <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="rpm">
